AIRPORT POLICE ++++++++++++++
The{Airport Police}check all passengers and baggage going through {customs.} As well as directing traffic, protecting the aircraft. Protection of the offices and shops. If there are any emergency landings the police deal with the{Fire Services and{Ambulances.}
If the Airport has been notified of a {Bomb scare}they call out the fire section and the ambulancemen. They then contact the aircraft and make it land at the other end of the runway. They then get the passengers out first then the luggage. They use a police dog to sniff out all the luggage throughout the plane.
